                        <td height="63"><img src="../global/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="1"> 
                           <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td bgcolor="#000000" height="8" width="100%" colspan="3"><span class="header">Choosing the Right Support Personnel</span></td></tr><tr><td bgcolor="#333399" height="2" width="41%"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td><td height="2" width="1%"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td><td height="2" width="58%" bgcolor="#FF9C00"><img src="/stccg/global/images/trek/glear.gif" width="1" height="5"></td></tr></table><TABLE WIDTH="100%" CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN=2><SPAN CLASS="header">Rating </SPAN><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/rating/8.gif" BORDER=0></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=28"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/read.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=28"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/review.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><A HREF="../membercenter/directory/memberpage.php3?member=1680">Matt "Figrin" Kirk</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Description</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%"><span class=text>An analysis of the various support personnel available, as well as recommendations for each affiliation, and emergency usage of support personnel.</span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><SPAN CLASS="header">Article</SPAN></TD><TD WIDTH="90%" ><span class=text>QUICK NOTE: I believe the last two articles posted have some unecessarily low ratings on them as a result of two sub-standard articles posted last night that were deleted. It seems that the articles numbers were replaced rather than skipped over, which caused the ratings for the poor articles to be transferred to the much improved articles. Anyway, on with the show...<br>
<br>
107. That&#146;s the amount of support personnel(SP) currently available in STCCG. But which is right for you? As with Assign Mission Specialists(AMS), your choice of a personnel that is so vital that you spent a seed slot on them, requires careful thought and planning. <br>
<br>
Here&#146;s the breakdown of SP by affiliation:<br>
<br>
Bajoran - 10<br>
Cardassian - 8<br>
Dominion - 9<br>
Federation - 37<br>
Ferengi - 1<br>
Klingon - 19<br>
Romulan - 14<br>
Non-Aligned - 9<br>
<br>
The two major ways to use Assign Support Personnel(ASP) that I have seen over the past few months since its release are:<br>
<br>
PROACTIVE<br>
This refers to usage by players who will download(d/l) their SP on their first turn, using them for staffing, preparing for mission attempts, or other uses, such as Prylar Mond to the Bajoran Shrine to &quot;conduct services&quot;. In any case, proactive SP are used mostly for offensive purposes. <br>
<br>
REACTIVE<br>
This refers to usage by players who will d/l their SP after hitting a wall dilemma (or finishing a mission), and needing specific skills to finish the job. Reactive SP are primarily defensive in use.<br>
<br>
Presented here are some examples of proactive/reactive SP usage that I have either used myself, or seen played by others:<br>
<br>
Bajoran<br>
-Prylar Mond (or Vedek Sorad) to the Shrine. First turn Orb Processing (without the Orb, of course... unless you self-seed an Orb + Sarjenka, then play HQ: Return Orb to Bajor 1st turn...)<br>
-Mora Pol. Prepare for those Scientific Methods with one of the best SP. Berserk Changeling and Odo&#146;s Cousin look a lot less scary when you have Mora Pol in your crew/Away Team(AT).<br>
<br>
Cardassian<br>
-Jural and/or Telle, setting up for the first/second turn Senior Staff Meeting(SSM). This is probably the most common use of SP that I&#146;ve seen. SP that have a skill as a classification go a long way to satisfying the requirements on SSM. You need OFF, SEC, MED, SCI, and ENG, so naturally, any one personnel who gives you two of these lessens the need for others during the initial attempt (which means you can save your important personnel for the second and third attempts). This is also known as red-shipping. Similar to red-shirting (see my article Dilemma Combos 102 for explanation), SP are VERY expendable in this use, and most players don&#146;t mind sacrificing them to achieve the ultimate goal of the game, which is the 100 points.<br>
<br>
Dominion<br>
-Temo&#146;Zuma and/or Yak&#146;Talon, SSM. Same idea, but would you rather have Transporter Skill or Computer Skill?<br>
-Lam for staffing Breen Warship. Can&#146;t find those darn Thots? Skip the unnecessary trip to the Alpha Quadrant to get them. Just d/l Breen Warship to your Primary Supply Depot, then get Lam aboard with ASP. Of course, you could just play Ready Room Door(RRD) and d/l its matching commander, Thot Gor, but the beauty of the seeded ASP is that you don&#146;t have to wait for it to show up in your hand. Make It So can help with this, but either way, Breen Warships are pretty nasty.<br>
<br>
Federation<br>
-Albert Einstein, for those annoying hologram decks. The only [Fed] hologram as an ASP, his high CUNNING should make those Ferengi Infestations look a lot more tolerable.<br>
-Dr. Selar, Sarek, or T&#146;Pan, for Vulcan decks. Believe it or not, there are more than enough Vulcans now to make a viable deck (even a Vulcan MS, Taurik!). Any one of these personnel can jump-start a Vulcan deck so you can start Mindmelding your way to victory.<br>
-Eric Pressman and/or Sarita Carson, SSM. As an additional bonus, Pressman can pass In the Pale Moonlight, historically difficult for the Feds (of course, not so hard anymore with Mirror personnel).<br>
-Deanna Troi. Got Empathy? She does. If you just cleared out First Contact but couldn&#146;t solve, d/l her. 30 points for you.<br>
-Fleet Adm. Shanthi and/or Morgan Bateson. Matching commanders as SP?? Yup. And the Feds have two of them, Shanthi probably having the more decent ship (USS Thunderchild), Bateson having the more useful skill (Stellar Cartography). Bateson, should in all fairness, have a [AU] icon; however, since he was released in Premiere, [AU] icons did not exist yet.<br>
-Kareel Odan, for Symbiont Diagnosis. Before you send Dax over to get the tar beat out of her by a nasty dilemma, consider Kareel Odan. Lack of Prep will be satisfied, as she is a Trill w/symbiont. And 9 INTEGRITY isn&#146;t too bad either.<br>
-Lt. D&#146;Amato, for dilemma busting. Geology x2, the man is a beast. Especially in [OS] decks when he gets bonus skills from Communicators or Tricorders.<br>
<br>
Ferengi<br>
-Prak. Well, what can you say about Prak. His stats are pretty decent for a Ferengi, his skills ain&#146;t bad, he has a command star, and he&#146;s universal (which means Lumba makes him Nav x2 + Stellar, which will get you past Nav Hazards and Gravimetric Distortion).<br>
<br>
Klingon<br>
-Kered, SSM. Archaeology isn&#146;t a bad secondary skill... wait, yeah it is. No dilemmas that I can think of off the top of my head require Archaeology. The only thing I can think of is either for mission requirements or to satisfy the Charybdis. But hey, he&#146;s [OS].<br>
-Divok, for Tribble defense. 10 Tribbles can be gross when you&#146;re playing Klingons (I know, I&#146;ve had it happen), but Divok can save your collective rear. Also, he&#146;s got Youth, a nice Isabella defense for the rogue PNZ deck you might encounter.<br>
-J&#146;Ddan, T&#146;Vor, and/or Wo&#146;Din, for extra SCIENCE. Klingons don&#146;t have a whole lot of SCIENCE, but with any one of these three, you should have enough.<br>
-Rukor, for dilemma busting. Need an OFFICER to either go in the box for Punishment Box, or stay on the ship for Crisis? Rukor&#146;s your man. He also helps out with Nav Hazards, Gravimetric Distortion, and Emergency Conversion.<br>
<br>
Romulan<br>
-Tomalak, matching commander. And not just any matching commander, he has a universal ship to captain (D&#146;deridex). This means first-turn Make It So use for Klingon players, after using Spacedoor to d/l the D&#146;deridex, then using ASP to get Tomalak aboard, then using Make It So to d/l RRD, which is used to d/l any Captain&#146;s Order (usually Captain&#146;s Log). One of ASP&#146;s stronger uses.<br>
-Mendak, matching commander. Not quite as utilitarian as Tomalak, but with a Reflection Therapy and Construct Starship, the Devoras comes out fairly quickly.<br>
-Bochra, for Hidden Fighter decks. How does this sound? You must have a Hidden Fighter and RRD in your hand. Discard ASP to d/l Bochra to your facility on or orbiting a planet. Send him outside, then play Hidden Fighter to d/l the Pi. Use RRD to d/l Patahk aboard, then use Make It So to d/l another RRD and get Captain&#146;s Log. Yet another quick way for the Romulan player to get big ships out quickly.<br>
<br>
Non-Aligned<br>
-Amaros, Test Propulsion Systems. Give this man a Flaxian Scout Vessel, and Lack of Preps at your Test Propulsion Systems are no more. Being Maquis doesn&#146;t hurt either, for that oddball Arms Deal you may face.<br>
-Gem, for dilemma-busting and/or Q-bypass. 9 INTEGRITY, and Emp x2, as well as being [AU] and [OS], make Gem a fairly decent choice in an OS deck.<br>
-Ty Kajada, SSM. Great for Ferengi players short on SECURITY personnel, she can also get past Dangerous Liaisons by herself, and she nets you 10 points from Royale Casino: Slots.<br>
<br>
Hope I&#146;ve given you some new ideas on ASP usage. Find your own unique use for this versatile card, and think of unorthodox ways to use SP to tip the balance in your STCCG games. Just think of them like the 211th Rule of Acquisition; &quot;Employees are the rungs on the ladder of success. Don&#146;t hesitate to step on them.&quot;<br>
<br>
Until next time,<br>
Figrin </span></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=28"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/read.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD><TD><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=28"><IMG SRC="/stccg/global/images/review.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN="TOP"><a href="articles.php3"><img src="/stccg/global/images/back.gif" border="0" ></a></TD><TD><a href="articleprint.php3?article=28" TARGET="BLANK_"><img src="/stccg/global/images/print.gif" border="0"></a></TD></TR></TABLE>
